<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,258,895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">Greenish-ochraceous (Plate III: A, B). Vertex with a central spot, two transversely striae, markings sometimes reduced to absent (Plate III: A, B, E, F). Frontoclypeus ochraceous, oblique striae in the lateral regions (Plate III: G). Forewing macropterous (Plate III: A, B).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,258,895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,380,402,427]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer basolateral cleft not membranous, darkly sclerotized part of pygofer side on posteroventral margin more than half its length, with small spines, dorsoapical margin without or with sparse small spinules (
<figureCitation box="[257,327,474,498]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[242,1350,241,1335]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,213,1372]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. (Paratype) Aconurella furcata sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: valve, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">
Figs 
<number box="[314,327,474,498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[363,378,474,498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
A); style apophysis three times length of preapical lobe (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1081,474,498]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[242,1350,241,1335]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,213,1372]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. (Paratype) Aconurella furcata sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: valve, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">
Figs 
<number box="[1068,1081,474,498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
D, 
<number box="[1116,1132,474,498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
C); connective furcate with arms widely divergent (
<figureCitation box="[416,485,510,534]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[242,1350,241,1335]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,213,1372]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. (Paratype) Aconurella furcata sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: valve, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">
Figs 
<number box="[472,485,510,534]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[517,532,510,534]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,258,895]" box="[201,714,546,571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,295,547,571]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">Female.</emphasis>
Sternite VII as shown in Plate III: D.
</paragraph>
