<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,258,895]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,691,715]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is tentatively described as distinct from 
<taxonomicName box="[929,1041,691,715]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Aconurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolixa">
<emphasis box="[929,946,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[962,1041,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">prolixa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both male specimens show some signs of poor development, i.e., the male pygofer basolateral cleft is not membranous (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1210,726,750]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[242,1350,241,1335]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,213,1372]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. (Paratype) Aconurella furcata sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: valve, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">
Figs 
<number box="[1197,1210,726,750]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number box="[1246,1261,726,750]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
A). In addition, the genitalia are weakly sclerotised in the 
<typeStatus box="[618,714,763,787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">paratype</typeStatus>
male. Distinguishing features of the species are the apophysis of style which is three times length of preapical lobe (
<figureCitation box="[718,787,798,822]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[242,1350,241,1335]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,213,1372]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. (Paratype) Aconurella furcata sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: valve, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">
Figs 
<number box="[774,787,798,822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
D, 
<number box="[822,837,798,822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
C) and the furcate connective with arms widely divergent (
<figureCitation box="[214,283,834,858]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,249,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[242,1350,241,1335]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,213,1372]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. (Paratype) Aconurella furcata sp. n. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: subgenital plate, ventral view; C: valve, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281807/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="34">
Figs 
<number box="[270,283,834,858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E, 
<number box="[315,331,834,858]" pageId="6" pageNumber="34" value="4.0">4</number>
D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
